Package: Interactions
Type: Package
Title: Plotting Marginal Effects of Regression Models
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Kirill Kalinin
Maintainer: The package maintainer <kkalinin@umich.edu>
Description: This package facilitates the estimation and visualization of marginal effects in complex scenarios by directly utilizing the variance-covariance matrix, rather than relying on the model object. Moreover, it offers flexibility by enabling the inclusion of multi-way interaction effects. The algorithm further allows users to specify the range of values for the variables of interest in the partial derivative of the regression equation.
